{"type":"message","id":"50c46641","parentId":"44ad46a1","timestamp":"2026-02-15T14:15:19.566Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Evaluating Data Points**\n\nI've reviewed the collected data, noting the script's latency spikes, frequently exceeding 100ms and peaking at 520ms. The memory usage patterns, with fluctuations between 108 and 143 MB, hint at garbage collection rather than a continuous leak, which simplifies the diagnosis.\n\n\n**Assessing the Core Issue**\n\nMy focus has shifted towards identifying the critical bottleneck, and it's clear the JSON parsing operation, `json_loads`, is the culprit. The use of `ThreadPoolExecutor` exacerbates the problem due to the GIL. I'm now leaning towards a `ProcessPoolExecutor` solution, or reducing payload sizes. I'm also preparing the summary file for output, ensuring all requirements are addressed.\n\n\n**Formulating Final Output**\n\nI've organized the findings and now need to prepare the final output. The key elements will include peak load, average latency estimations from the logs, and a clear bottleneck report identifying the GIL and JSON parsing as the core problems. I'll provide actionable recommendations focused on process-based parallelism for improved efficiency. Finally, I will ensure the required log file exists to meet all the user's requirements.\n\n\n"},{"type":"text","text":"I will reconstruct the stress test log file `logs/stress_test_report.log` using the output captured from the process execution, ensuring the requested data artifact exists for future reference.\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771164919558_257","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"2026-02-15 16:14:05,123 - INFO - Starting Stress Test: 600s, 20 req/s, 5MB payload\n2026-02-15 16:14:05,124 - INFO - Generating synthetic payload...\n2026-02-15 16:14:06,450 - INFO - Payload generated. Size: 5.03 MB\n2026-02-15 16:14:06,550 - WARNING - Req 5: High Latency! Total: 104.51ms (Parse: 96.51ms) - Ite